<!-- Introduction -->
 <purpose>
This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the representation of 
   assignments of properties. This module provides the constructs for the representation of an assignment of property. However, it does not list the concepts to which such an assignment can be done.
<note>That list shall be defined in the application modules that use the present application module.
</note> 
 </purpose>

 <inscope>
	<li>assignment of a property to product data;</li>
    <li>use of an independent property in the definition of an item;</li>
	<li>association of a representation with a property;</li>
	<li>items within the scope of application module <module_ref linkend="foundation_representation:1_scope">Foundation representation</module_ref>, ISO/TS 10303-1006;</li>
	<li>items within the scope of application module <module_ref linkend="independent_property:1_scope">Independent property</module_ref>, ISO/TS 10303-1036.</li>
 </inscope>

 <outscope>
	<li>relationships between properties;</li>
	<li>definition of independent property types;</li>
	<li>shape property and properties derived from shape characteristics;</li>
	<li>properties characterizing activity data.</li>
 </outscope>

